            <section id="about" class="section">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> About This Project</h2>
                <div class="info-section">
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This Iris Flower Classification project was developed as a demonstration of machine learning concepts applied to botanical classification. The application allows users to input measurements of iris flowers and receive a classification prediction based on a machine learning model.</p>
                        
                        <p>The Iris flower data set is a classic multivariate data set introduced by the British statistician and biologist Ronald Fisher in his 1936 paper. It is sometimes called Anderson's Iris data set because Edgar Anderson collected the data to quantify the morphologic variation of Iris flowers of three related species.</p>
                        
                        <p>This project was created by <strong>Mohseen Rangrez</strong> as part of a demonstration for web-based machine learning applications. The interface combines educational content about iris flowers with an interactive classification tool.</p>
                        
                        <p>For more information about the technical implementation or to access the source code, please visit the project repository on GitHub.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
